  "prompt": "What is the best way of combining multiple jpegs into one jpeg/PDF on Mac OS X?",
  "response": "Combining multiple JPEGs into one JPEG or a PDF on macOS can be done in several ways. Here are a couple of the most straightforward methods:\n\n### Method 1: Using Preview (for PDF)\n\n1. **Open Preview**:\n   - Select all the JPEG files you want to combine in Finder, right-click, and choose **Open With > Preview**.\n\n2. **Combine Images**:\n   - Once the images are open in Preview, you should see a sidebar with thumbnails of each image. If the sidebar is not visible, go to **View > Thumbnails**.\n   - Rearrange the images in the sidebar by dragging them into the desired order.\n\n3. **Export as PDF**:\n   - Go to **File > Print** (or press Command + P).\n   - In the print dialog, click on the **PDF** button at the bottom-left corner and select **Save as PDF**.\n   - Choose your save location and file name, then click **Save**.\n\n### Method 2: Using Preview (for JPEG)\n\n1. **Open Preview**:\n   - Select all the JPEG files you want to combine in Finder, right-click, and choose **Open With > Preview**.\n\n2. **Select All and Copy**:\n   - With the images open in Preview, select all thumbnails in the sidebar (Command + A), then go to **Edit > Copy** (or press Command + C).\n\n3. **Create a New Image**:\n   - Go to **File > New from Clipboard** (or press Command + N). This will create a new document with the first image.\n\n4. **Add Additional Images**:\n   - For each additional image, go to the new document, select **Edit > Paste** (or press Command + V). You may need to adjust the position of the images to your liking.\n\n5. **Export as JPEG**:\n   - Once you have all images combined on one canvas, go to **File > Export**, select **JPEG** from the format dropdown, and choose your desired quality and save location.\n\n### Method 3: Using Automator (for PDF)\n\n1. **Open Automator**:\n   - Open Automator from your Applications folder.\n\n2. **Create New Workflow**:\n   - Choose **New Document**, then select **Workflow**.\n\n3. **Set Up Workflow**:\n   - In the left panel, search for **Get Specified Finder Items** and drag it to the right panel.\n   - Add a **New PDF from Images** action (found under **PDFs**).\n\n4. **Run the Workflow**:\n   - Add the JPEG files to the **Get Specified Finder Items** section, then run the workflow. This will create a PDF from the selected images.\n\n### Notes:\n- For combining images into a single JPEG, you may need to adjust the canvas size to fit all images, which can be more complex than creating a PDF.\n- There are also third-party applications like **Adobe Acrobat**, **GIMP**, or **ImageMagick** that can provide more advanced options for combining images.\n\nChoose the method that best fits your needs!",
